                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; a few lines on
                           the incipit page of the text, alternating with black lines; two initial
                           lines of each section of the text; names of Hebrew letters in Ps. 118
                           (e.g., fols. 30vb, 32ra, 33vb); parts of abbreviations; some other words,
                           e.g., ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols.7vb, 8rb, 23ra), wa-kāʿǝba (e.g., fols. 9ra,
                           29va, 31rb), wa-yǝbälu (fols. 11va, 13ra), qǝdmä wängel (e.g., fols.
                           27va, 29rb, 32va); elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals
                           or their elements.</seg>
